    "department": "Global Brand \u0026 MKT Center",
    "description": "Job Position: Germany PR Specialist\n\nLocation: Berlin/Amsterdam\n\n\nABOUT PLAUD INC.\n\nPlaud is building the world's most trusted AI work companion for professionals to elevate productivity and performance through note-taking solutions, loved by over 1,000,000 users worldwide since 2023. With a mission to amplify human intelligence, Plaud is building the next-generation intelligence infrastructure and interfaces to capture, extract, and utilize what you say, hear, see, and think.\n\nPlaud Inc. is a Delaware-incorporated, San Francisco-based company pushing the boundary of human–AI intelligence through a hardware–software combination. With ISO 27001, ISO 27701, GDPR, SOC 2, HIPAA, and EN 18031 compliance, Plaud is committed to the highest standards of data security and privacy protection.\n\nTo learn more about Plaud, please visit http://www.plaud.ai/https://www.plaud.ai and follow along on Instagram https://www.instagram.com/plaud_official/, X https://twitter.com/PLAUDAI, Facebook https://www.facebook.com/plaudai, LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/plaudai/?viewAsMember=true, and YouTube https://www.youtube.com/@PLAUDAI\n\n\n\n\n\nWHY YOU SHOULD JOIN US\n\nPlaud is building the next generation intelligence infrastructure and interfaces to capture, extract, and utilize intelligence from what people say, hear, see, and think.\n\n - Plaud is a bootstrapped, skyrocketing, profitable company with a $250M revenue run rate achieved in just three years.\n\n - Define the next-gen paradigm for human-AI interaction.\n\n - Gain exposure to cutting-edge AI for Pro tools and play a direct role in our global expansion.\n\n - Work with passionate teammates who value innovation, collaboration, and customer success.\n\n - Grow your career in a culture that champions continuous learning and fast career development.\n\n - Market-competitive compensation, global exposure, and a vibrant, creativity-fueled work atmosphere.\n\n\nWHAT YOU WILL DO\n\n - Strategy \u0026 Planning: Develop and execute global and regional PR strategies for Plaud Consumer, Business, and Developer sectors; Identify key narratives to position Plaud as a pioneer in AI-driven productivity; Coordinate launches, thought leadership campaigns, and brand moments across major markets.\n\n - Media Relations: Build and manage relationships with tier-1 tech, business, and vertical media; Secure consistent, high-quality coverage across earned media channels; Act as day-to-day contact for press inquiries, briefings, and interviews.\n\n - Content \u0026 Messaging: Draft press releases, media pitches, briefing documents, op-eds, and bylines; Ensure message consistency across external channels; Collaborate with product, legal, and marketing teams to develop PR-ready narratives.\n\n - Event \u0026 Communications: Support media strategies for product launches, global conferences, and press events; Prepare spokespeople with media training and talking points; Manage sentiment.\n\n - Analytics \u0026 Optimization: Track PR performance and coverage using relevant tools; Analyze campaign impact and iterate based on insights; Maintain and grow a database of press contacts, coverage reports, and benchmarks.\n\n\nMINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS\n\n - 2+ years of PR experience, preferably in tech, AI, SaaS, or premium consumer electronics.\n\n - Native in German; Proficient in English.\n\n - Proven track record of securing high-impact media coverage in global markets.\n\n - Strong media network across business, tech, and verticals.\n\n - Excellent storytelling, writing, and editing skills.\n\n - Comfortable navigating fast-paced, international environments with shifting priorities.\n\n - Experience working with executive stakeholders, agencies, and cross-functional teams.\n\n - Good at using AI tools to improve work efficiency.\n\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n - Experience working in fast-paced, international environments with shifting priorities.\n\n - Demonstrated success working with C-suite executives, external agencies, and cross-functional teams.\n\n - Background in AI, productivity tools, or consumer technology sectors.\n\n - Experience managing product launch communications and global conference strategies.\n\n - Track record of thought leadership campaign development and execution.\n\nDisclaimer: Plaud is and will continue to be an equal opportunity employer. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, age, veteran status, disability, genetic information, or other applicable legally protected characteristics.",
